  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing the immediate needs of older people and their families in cyclone affected districts of Inhambane, Mozambique</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">500 household with an estimated number of 2500 members, among them orphan children, people with disabilities and other vulnerable women and men.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to provide life-saving support and reduce the vulnerability of 500 households in greatest need living in 2 communities in 2 district of rural Inhambane (Massinga and Inhambane town) by providing a basic family support kit which includes a number of NFI detailed below, iron sheeting and repairs to one government older people&apos;s home. These will be 500 households identified as acutely vulnerable, this could be because of chronic disease, or disability or if there are orphaned or other vulnerable children. The project will be implemented in partnership with a local partner APOSEMO and in collaboration with the local and national disaster management committees. The project is in line with the government response plan and the UN response plan on shelter and protection.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide urgent emergency relief to older people headed households and households with people living with disabilities affected by cyclone Dineo and support them to prepare for their recovery in the districts of Massinga and Inhambane town in Inhambane Province</narrative>
  </description>
